snippet.textDisplay:
...Weren't some ARM cores also affected by Meltdown and one or more Spectre variants? I don't see how Apple moving to a different ISA will automatically immune to the kind of speculative execution vulnerabilities found on Intel CPUs?

Because Apple makes their own customized ARM cores, while they have to buy the Intel CPUs as-is and potentially vulnerable to whatever security issues Intel's engineers didn't care about or missed, I guess Apple moving Macs to ARM could make a difference, or at least give them more control over whether their CPUs are vulnerable or not, but. That doesn't technically have anything to do with ARM specifically? In theory, Apple could do the same thing with Risc-V.
